---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | The Canary Institute" description="Learn about The Canary Institute's mission, team, and approach to AI policy research and advocacy.">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Who We Are</h2>
    <p>
      The Canary Institute is an independent, non-partisan, not-for-profit
      organization dedicated to ensuring that the development of advanced
      artificial intelligence proceeds safely and in the public interest. Our
      name reflects our purpose: like the canary in the coal mine, we aim to
      detect and communicate dangers before they become catastrophic.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Canary Institute was founded in 2026 by Daniel Parshall, Ph.D., a
      former physicist and data scientist, in response to the widening gap
      between the warnings issued by AI's own architects and the policy
      frameworks needed to act on them. The leading figures in AI
      research (including Nobel laureates, Turing Award winners, and the
      heads of major AI laboratories) have publicly stated that the
      technology they are building may pose an existential threat to humanity.
      When the architects themselves issue warnings of this gravity, civil
      society must respond with institutions equal to the challenge.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Our Approach</h2>
    <p>
      AI policy pulls from a lot of fields: ML, economics, governance,
      law, ethics. We don't think one set of specialists is going to
      solve it.
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not opposed to artificial intelligence. We are opposed to
      negligence. The benefits are real; so are the risks. Our work
      assumes you can take both seriously at once, and that the policy
      choices about meaningful human control are the ones that decide
      which side wins.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Our Principles</h2>

    <div class="principles-grid">
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Evidence Over Ideology</h3>
        <p>
          We follow the science and the data wherever they lead. We do not begin
          from a conclusion. If the evidence says the risks are lower than
          feared, we will say so. If higher, we will say that too.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Non-Partisan Independence</h3>
        <p>
          AI policy is not a left or right issue. It is a human issue. We accept
          no corporate funding that conditions our work, and we align with no
          political party or movement.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Clarity Without Distortion</h3>
        <p>
          The public deserves to understand what is happening. We translate
          technical research into accessible language without sensationalism or
          false reassurance.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle">
        <h3>Urgency Without Panic</h3>
        <p>
          The timelines for advanced AI capabilities are uncertain but may be
          short. This demands focused, serious action: not paralysis, not
          complacency, and not hysteria.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Team</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Founder and Director</strong><br />
      Daniel Parshall, Ph.D., former physicist and data scientist.
      Coauthor, <em>Measuring AI's Economic Reach</em> (Canary Institute /
      GWU Center for Economic Research, 2026).
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Board of Directors and Advisors</strong><br />
      The Institute's governance structure is being formalized in 2026.
      Announcements forthcoming.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .principles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .principles-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .principle {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .principle h3 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .principle p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
